node.text: We all have an edge. We all are floating our psyche on top with a great ocean underneath.  Brad Dourif  Each of us is a drop in the ocean, but we all like to think that we are on top of the water. However, each of us has its limits and reaching the peak is unfortunate in some of the fields. What is your edge?

The economy is totally upside-down nowadays and the most disposable people are the lower class ones. While white collars remain untouched, blue collars strive for their wage and remain hopeless when they lose their job or get a cut from their salary. Try to stick with the upper half!

The chase of excellence has been nowadays highly emphasized by people who think and know that they are capable of more. They do not stop at good. They do not stop even at best. They seek for the highest achievable result and they would still want more. How's 10 out of 10 for you?
Great minds discuss ideas; average minds discuss events; small minds discuss people.  Eleanor Roosevelt
Focus on the future than stay stuck in the past. Checking the rearview mirror is good, but the road ahead is much more important!

If you have the right ideas and the required energy to bring them to reality, you will definitely achieve wealth, both physically and psychically. It is all about your dedication to your thoughts and how much you believe in yourself!
You want a change? Be prepared to completely leave the old you if you want to become someone else. Letting go of the past is the hardest part!
Invest your money wisely and you will truly be grateful to the wealth you own!
If you were able to dream something, you definitely can do it. You just need to remember that part in the dream when you actually did it!
Every experience, good or bad, is a priceless collector's item.  Isaac Marion
It's how you feel about yourself that's going to count in all your behavioral changes. The higher the self-esteem, the better the change will be. Believe in yourself!
Sometimes when you innovate, you make mistakes. It is best to admit them quickly, and get on with improving your other innovations.  Steve Jobs

History is littered with inventors who had -great- ideas but kept them quiet and then poorly executed them. And history is lit up with do-ers who took ideas that were floating around in the ether and actually made something happen. In fact, just about every successful venture is based on an unoriginal idea, beautifully executed. So, if you've got ideas, let them go! They're probably holding you back from the hard work of actually executing.
You only get to know how valuable is hard work when you input that hard work yourself!

As great as the quote from Confucius is, the sad truth is that doing what you love is the dream of many, but the reality of few. There are only two things you need to get any job; belief in yourself and desire. The rest will somehow take care of itself. Are you doing the job you love?
Fashion fosters cliches of beauty, but I want to tear them apart.  Miuccia Prada

When you think of something for a long time, you slowly become what you think of: you imagine yourself in that position and you live by those values, simulating success almost unconsciously. Think big and become bigger!

You build on failure. You use it as a stepping stone. Close the door on the past. You don't try to forget the mistakes, but you don't dwell on it. You don't let it have any of your energy, or any of your time, or any of your space.  Johnny Cash
It's not quite enough to try. Yes, it is a big part of the deal, but in order to triumph, you have to go the extra mile!
You have to keep innovating in order to keep your success up high. However, innovation brings failure, so if you didn't fail until now, you've never innovated enough!
Losers visualize the penalties of failure. Winners visualize the rewards of success.  William S. Gilbert

Before you speak, listen. Before you write, think. Before you spend, earn. Before you invest, investigate. Before you criticize, wait. Before you pray, forgive. Before you quit, try. Before you retire, save. Before you die, give.  William A. Ward
People classify you by your attitude. They also steal attitudes they like from people they worship, so make yours worth the catch!
Love without action is meaningless and action without love is irrelevant!
Focus on the journey, not the destination. Joy is found not in finishing an activity but in doing it.  Greg Anderson

I think the purpose of life is to be useful, to be responsible, to be honorable, to be compassionate. It is, after all, to matter: to count, to stand for something, to have made some difference that you lived at all!
Don't let life discourage you; everyone who got where he is had to begin where he was.  Richard L. Evans

Your content has to be powerful and original if you want it to be discussed by people as a trend. If people never heard about you or what you do, you have a serious problem, and you are the only one to fix it. Create original content!
Curiosity enhances both knowledge and creativity. It's good to be curious of things, as long as it doesn't bother other people around. Search and you will find!
Madness is badness of spirit, when one seeks profit from all sources.  Aristotle
Just like your body and lifestyle can be healthy or unhealthy, the same is true with your beliefs. Your beliefs can be your medicine or your poison.  Steve Maraboli

Survival is for the human animal; fear the motivation. For the spiritual being survival is irrelevant. Curiosity, compassion and creativity are the name of the game; unconditional love the motivation!

All change is not growth, as all movement is not forward. -Ellen Glasgow-  We tend to resist change, unless we seek it out. When we do seek it out, it's because we are told that change is good and we need to get out of our comfort zone to make any progress at all. Nevertheless, when we make changes, they must be calculated and for the better. Make sure that you are moving forward and not simply moving!
Save a part of your income and begin now, for the man with a surplus controls circumstances and the man without a surplus is controlled by circumstances. �Henry Buckley
Opportunity is missed by most people because it is dressed in overalls and looks like work!

We all have the same shot at success; we just have to strive for it in order to make progresses in that area. We are all born alone and without anything that could advantage us. So remember, all you gain in life is technically all profit, because you start with zero!
Let go of things that prevent you from being rich. Focus on the present situation and you will get to keep your money. Success is waiting for you!
The first sentence of a book is a handshake, perhaps an embrace.  Jhumpa Lahiri

We wear chains we've forged in life. Some ask for help getting rid of them, yet rarely does that help come dramatically. Try to dive into this realistically and so much time will be spent on what really is a false belief and then which false beliefs are binding us too tightly and which provide necessary support to living. Is there one person on the planet whose view of reality is the best?
If you don't see yourself as a winner, then you cannot perform as a winner!
The only thing that will stop you from succeeding are the buts you use to make excuses!
Stop showing off ? it doesn't pay off at all. Worse, it attracts unwanted attention. You might as well want to put a target on your back. Stop living for other people!

Intelligence is an elusive concept. There's a certain sharpness, an ability to absorb new facts. To walk into a situation, have something explained to you and immediately say, -Well, what about this?- To ask an insightful question. To absorb it in real time. A capacity to remember. To relate to domains that may not seem connected at first. A certain creativity that allows people to be effective!
Believe in yourself and your skills and you will be able to use them for your own better life!

Profit is at least equal to input, in a business. If your output does not exceed what you invest, there is no profit, and you as an entrepreneur will have no value. Contribute to production if you want to increase profit!

Nothing is impossible; you just have to keep trying doing it. Taking down ways to do it one by one while trying to solve one problem is way more likely to have a positive outcome than not knowing what your options would be at all. Don't ever say that something cannot be done, because it can. It's just that no one figured out how to do it yet.
Motivation is a fire from within. If someone else tries to light that fire under you, chances are it will burn very briefly.  Stephen R. Covey

Your goal as an investor should simply be to purchase, at a rational price, a part interest in an easily-understandable business whose earnings are virtually certain to be materially higher five, ten and twenty years from now. Over time, you will find only a few companies that meet these standards - so when you see one that qualifies, you should buy a meaningful amount of stock. You must also resist the temptation to stray from your guidelines: If you aren't willing to own a stock for ten years, don't even think about owning it for ten minutes. Put together a portfolio of companies whose aggregate earnings march upward over the years, and so also will the portfolio's market value. �Warren Buffett
Without an idea, nothing can start working, so quit wasting any more time and let your creativity run wild!

Ambition is the first step to success. The second is action. Be active in what you want to achieve, truly embrace it and make it a part of your life. Build it up a little, every day, and success will be at your feet. Strength and growth come only through continuous effort and struggle, so start working!
You are the hero of your own story and you are the only one who can do something that can be brilliant through your eyes. Try to contribute rather than comment foreign work!

To be a good father and mother requires that the parents defer many of their own needs and desires in favor of the needs of their children. It takes courage, determination, commitment, toughness and heart for parents to put into practice the selfless truth that the youngsters need so much in learning how to deal with life. Invest in your children's future!
Dream big. Start small. Act now!
The best career advice to give the young is, find out what you like doing best and get someone else to pay you for doing it!
Strategy without tactics is the slowest route to victory, tactics without strategy is the noise before defeat.  Sun Tsu
I wandered everywhere, through cities and countries wide. And everywhere I went, the world was on my side!

You can't say you've hiked all the paths of your life until you've mastered raw, face-to-face, honest conversations. Those are the keys to openness and the lessons that teach you how to understand people. When you understand people, you understand their thinking and when you understand people's thinking, you finally understand their strategy of business. Focus on really knowing your people, and your people will help you work your way up the society's ladder!

Legendary martial artist Bruce Lee didn't just kick ass as a fighter. He also possessed a fine line in punchy philosophy, spitting countless memorable inspirational quips during his incredibly accomplished, too-short life and career as an actor, director, writer and instructor. Focus on everything you do and it will all end in success!

Everything that happens around you is a perfect reflection of what is going around in your microenvironment. Before studying any situation, look inside and find the thing that changed it. You are the only one who influences your life!

Without being perseverant, one can never meet success. There is no such thing as quitting whenever you want to and still making it. You have to push yourself harder each time and stay with your eyes on the prize!
People take different roads seeking fulfillment and happiness. Just because they're not on your road doesn't mean they've gotten lost!
If you have the will to win, you have achieved half your success; if you don't, you have achieved half your failure!
Girls do not dress for boys. They dress for themselves and, of course, each other. If girls dressed for boys they'd just walk around naked at all times.  Betsey Johnson

Don't spend your life constantly being dissatisfied and unhappy and always wanting something else than it has to offer. Learn your powers, emphasize your abilities and make the best of who you are, and you'll fall in love with the person you'll become!
Richness always triggers people to show their true selves, so there's no change involved. Money will get your greed on the surface!
Do not hurry when you do anything. Take all the time you need and deliver a good output, whether it is complicated or not. Better to do it well than fast!
Without failure, there is no innovation. The balance has to go down if you want it to go higher than it ever was. You build success on failure!
Material wealth can be bad for your health. Because when you're in the soil it'll make your blood boil, that you couldn't keep it all for your self.  Benny Bellamacina
To understand the heart and mind of a person, look not at what he has already achieved, but at what he aspires to do!

Always keep your head up and remain strong on your feet, don't let the others take you down. When they put spikes on your dance floor, learn how to waltz between them, they'll eventually know you for the better one and take a step back, letting you take the whole stage.
Trust is maybe the most hunted concept in business and it is very hard to find trustworthy people nowadays. But when you do, show them your trust and they will definitely respond!
Your self-worth is determined by you. You don't have to depend on someone telling you who you are.  Beyonce Knowles
A person's highest peaks indirectly represent its mind and its intelligence's boundaries. Aim high and you will be considered wise!
Perfection cannot be acquired, but it is important that you are comfortable with yourself and believe in your skills. The more you think about yourself as whole, the greater the success will be!

Oprah�came from very humble origins, but she learned that the trick to overcoming racism, sexism, and prejudice was simply to do her best and reap the well-earned benefits. One of those benefits was to know that if she chased excellence, people would begin to judge her for her work, not by the�color of her skin.I was raised to believe that excellence is the best deterrent to racism or sexism. And that's how I operate my life.  Oprah Winfrey
Content builds relationships. Relationships are built on trust. Trust drives revenue!
Financial security is much more important than money itself. You need to keep your money, not only to have it. Invest in the safety of your assets!
Each today, well-lived, makes yesterday a dream of happiness and each tomorrow a vision of hope. Look, therefore, to this one day, for it and it alone is life!
I'm a businesswoman who's serious about her money. I want an empire.  Toni Braxton

We should be thinking about social and search as channels that need an unified approach, because the best content should appeal to both channels and the cross-over benefits/economies of scale are potentially huge!
Wealth, my son, should never be your goal in life. Your words are eloquent but they are mere words. True wealth is of the heart, not of the purse.  Og Mandin
Time is priceless and time is money. But what you do with your time is the most important factor in defining a psychological pattern in every person. Use your time wisely!
You will need to learn how to act like a white-collar if you want to be considered a white-collar!
Believe in yourself, take on your challenges, dig deep within yourself to conquer fears. You got to keep going so that your future shine as bright as you can imagine. Never let anyone bring you down!
You can measure opportunity with the same yardstick that measures the risk involved. They go together.  Earl Nightingale
Leadership means influencing the people you have beyond you. Remember, you are setting a certain state of mind and you have to do it right in order for it to be shared properly. Be a leader!
Invest in yourself first. Expect nothing from no one and be willing to work for everything.  Tony Gaskins
I have never worked a day in my life without selling. If i believe in something, I sell it, and I sell it hard.  Estee Lauder

Believing in ourselves can be difficult, especially if we find that there are others who don't. Sometimes, to our disappointment, we find that the individuals who we thought would have the most faith in us, don't. We discover that somewhere along the line, they started doubting us more than believing in us. However, we cannot always depend on others. We need to learn to have faith in ourselves, to realize that we are capable of getting through our struggles and accomplishing our goals. Just because we may fall down at times, does not mean that we can't get up and succeed. Believe!
Make your brand visible on the internet by targeting it to the right niche and increasing its traffic and conversion rates. Market your brand!

Content Marketing is a more competitive environment certainly, but those who have real empathy for web users and influencers AND have the SEO skills to infuse their work with great keyword targeting, search accessibility, etc., are going to have ongoing success!
Education is what will prevent you from failing. Invest in knowledge and you will encounter the greatest return!
Every day, every step forward cumulates into something big and beautiful. Think long-term!
It’s not that 'content is king,' but content certainly is the Hand of the King!
It's a good idea to understand how to work with Bing and Google for maximum SEO and ranking benefit!
It takes 20 years to build a reputation and five minutes to ruin it. If you think about that, you'll do things differently!
Running with the herd is not always a great idea; be unique, and the links will come!
Ordinary people love entertainment. Extraordinary people adore education.
Today it's not about 'get the traffic' -- it's about 'get the targeted and relevant traffic!
